    "en": "Many components used in electric or electronic circuits have a (mostly unwanted) inductance, e.g., the inductance of the connecting leads of a resistor. Such parasitic inductances are in most cases not the main purpose of the component and thus should not be taken as a rationale for classifying the component as an inductor."
  },
